[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Anomaly 1.5.3
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stalkeranomaly/mods/102]xlibs[/url]
[*]MCM
[/list]

[size=3][b]Install (MO2)[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Install xlibs
[*]Install AlifeBalance
[*]Load order does not matter
[*]Configure via MCM
[/list]

[size=3][b]Uninstall (MO2)[/b][/size]
Disable or remove in MO2.

[size=3][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]
Tested with vanilla Anomaly 1.5.3 and GAMMA modpack.
Does not modify base scripts. Does not call alife_create or SIMBOARD:create_squad.

[line]

[size=3][b]Architecture[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]AlifeBalance runs on xlibs, a reverse-engineered API that wraps the X-Ray engine source.
[*]No base script edits, no engine patches. Runtime callbacks only.
[*]Trip queue is frame-spread via xslice to smooth combat bursts.
[*]See doc/architecture.md for full design documentation.
[/list]

[size=3][b]Credits[/b][/size]
Altogolik - support, ideas, source materials

[size=3][b]Usage and License[/b][/size]
Modpacks: allowed and encouraged. Keep the readme and license files.
Addons, patches, integrations: allowed. Credit "AlifeBalance by Damian Sirbu" visibly on your mod page.
Reproducing the implementation in other software: not allowed, even with credit.
Full license in LICENSE file and on GitHub.

